website_summaries.verdict: This high-protein, low carb blend of chicken, lamb and mussel is recommended for all cats from kittens to senior felines. Mixing with water is recommended although some cats like it dry.
pros: Has a 99 percent meat content, thanks to barn-raised chicken, free range lamb and green-lipped mussel from New Zealand
No gluten, wheat, soy or rice
cons: May be too chewy for some cats who are missing teeth or have other oral problems

customer_reviews.title: Cats LOVE IT!
customer_reviews.text: All four of my cats love this cat food and flavor. My cats are finicky and that's an understatement. It's near impossible to get all four cats to like the same food, but they all devour this. It's also my understanding that New Zealand has stricter guidelines for cat food than the USA which makes this even better as far as I am concerned. I also noticed one of my cats had coarse hair that always seemed to get matted who now has soft fur that doesn't get matted anymore after being on this food exclusively for about a month.
customer_reviews.author: QT

customer_reviews.title: Winner winner chicken/lamb or salmon/lamb dinner!!
customer_reviews.text: Omg, this cat has never eaten anything like he's eating this! 11 yrs of trying everything for sensitive digestion, no grain, wet food, dry food, raw, even another brand of freeze dried, all very expensive, and usually no luck. We have had some luck with one brand (RC)of dry for sensitive digestion, but always hard to get him back on it after one of his vomiting spells. We received this today, and this is his second meal, small to start of course, but he's never wanted seconds on anything, ever!! If you have a very fussy eater, try this, it's a winner!
customer_reviews.author: Punnie

customer_reviews.title: Top quality food = Healthier cats!
customer_reviews.text: I have 2 cats (15-yr-old female & 3-yr-old male) & they have different tastes, so finding food they both like is sometimes a challenge. They both love this brand of food & I have seen a difference in their health (less shedding & fewer hairballs for the long-haired one). I DO believe that a couple months of this has contributed to some weight gain by both (initially the younger cat lost a bit), so we've started cutting back their portions. Our vet says that since they still have access to dry food, they only need the amount of meat in a mouse's body once/day. The recommended portions are much too large for normal cats.
customer_reviews.author: K. Williams

customer_reviews.title: Bearcat Loves it!
customer_reviews.text: Bear loves it! Mr. Dry Food Only says yum. I like it because it doesn't smell and I can portion out the amount he will eat at one time. No waste. And it is high in protein and good for him, but don't tell him. We have been feeding this for about a month. We notice an increase in his energy level.
customer_reviews.author: Susan

customer_reviews.title: Order for finicky eaters
customer_reviews.text: This food is great. My finicky female feline loves a little of this crumbled over anything. Or with a little water mixed in to crumbles. She can’t eat much of variety so I really appreciate a food she loves. My only complaint is Amazons shopping packed it with an item that had a horrific scent and left that on the cat food bag as well. Ugh. Who does that?? My cat doesn’t want to smell sandalwood and sachets with lamb and salmon.
customer_reviews.author: Amy H

customer_reviews.title: Purchased a few times
customer_reviews.text: One of my cats waits for me to put this into his bowl. I think it is high quality and he has a sensitive stomach so I'm glad he likes it. I just wish he loved something that was cheaper! He likes this one and the salmon but doesn't care for the beef particularly.
customer_reviews.author: NinaTop Contributor: Makeup

customer_reviews.title: Buy this product! I have one of the most finicky eaters in the planet!
customer_reviews.text: It’s a great deal and since putting my car on an all raw foods diet I use this particular mix in with bland meats that she’s not to keen on. And she’s. A dining eater. As a tip for other new pet owners especially cat, stick with food that was winged when alive, seafood is so dangerous now days. Chicken, duck turkey. I love this brand for freeze dried raw food as a mix in. It’s great! Well at least my cat thinks so. Don’t be afraid to mix this in with chicken or duck.
customer_reviews.author: Shane Throckmorton

customer_reviews.title: Kitties loved flavor of nutritional meal
customer_reviews.text: Just tried two flavors (chicken/lamb & salmon/lamb) and 2 out of 3 kitties just love the salmon so I mix some of the chicken and lamb in with the salmon. They like it as a meal, also as a meal topper. I couldn’t find anywhere on the pkg if the food is freeze dried or not. Bought this in attempt of getting free range meats high in nutrients for our senior kitties. Already need to restock.
customer_reviews.author: Nancy V.

customer_reviews.title: Pricey, but my two picky girls love it
customer_reviews.text: My 14 year old will not eat anything but Science Diet SO. Only food she wants. LOL But I'd like her having more protein and less crap. She eats this as a topper or "treat" all the time. It's amazing. She will turn her nose up to it if she's not hungry thought. Meanwhile, my 7 month old kitten LOVES these as a topper or treat. I put it over her grain free dried food or as a treat. She comes running when she knows I have the bag. It's expensive, so that's the reason I give it a 4 star. My protein doesn't cost as much as this product! lol

customer_reviews.title: The pickiest cat loves this food!
customer_reviews.text: I have a 1 year old who will eat just about anything. Then I have a 15 year old queen of the castle. ALL she would ever eat is SO (science diet) grain. No wet food, no other dried food, and rarely even fresh chicken. Well, I bought this for my little one, and low and behold...FIFI LOVES IT! Ms Queenie eats it dry. She guzzles it down. In fact, she will wake me up at all hours in the middle of the night just to get me to give her some. LOL I wish I had learned of this stuff 10 years ago.
customer_reviews.author: Kachinkie

customer_reviews.title: Finicky Cats love it.
customer_reviews.text: It's the second one I am trying on my cat who is very finicky. Though costly he would rather starve than eat 90% of the food I offered thru the years. Tons of money down the drain in soft organic foods he hated. My rating is down because it is again crushed. Amazon's mistake, stickers on bags ( both) said ship in box and both came in plastic sleeves, product powdered mostly. It is not as appealing to my cat in mush form. But, all said he likes this one also.
customer_reviews.author: queenkimlee

customer_reviews.title: Beware -- This will spoil your cat(s)!
customer_reviews.text: We call this "kitty crack" as our cats love it so much. We use it for treats for them, and occasionally make a meal out of it for them by adding some goat milk to make sure they get enough liquid to help digest the freeze-dried pellets. They LOVE this stuff -- all the flavors. We have learned to keep some on hand at all times or suffer the consequences -- and those of you that have cats know "that look" when your cat demands something and you know that you'd better get it for them or they will make you regret life in general!
customer_reviews.author: Karma Yoakem

customer_reviews.title: Plastic smell
customer_reviews.text: My 3 cats love freeze-dried food, but the New Zealand Feline Natural made 2 of them sick and throw up. Ingredients are top but the smell is terrible, nothing like the other freeze dried food I'm feeding to them. The smell is hard to describe, smells like plastic or something long stored and taking on plastic smell? I only gave each cat a few pellets and 2 of them started to throw up within 20 minutes. When offered a couple of days later all 3 of them walked away. The food is too expensive to be smelling like plastic and wasted.
customer_reviews.author: Conny

customer_reviews.title: My picky eater loves it!
customer_reviews.text: My fur baby is a picky eater, and loves the Lamb & King Salmon Feast flavor! I was introduced to this product from my holistic vet. I recently switched my cat to a grain-free diet and feed her this Feline Natural Grain-Free Freeze Dried Cat Food now in place of kibble. I leave a bowl out 24/7 so she has something to graze on between her wet food meals. She goes though about 1 (11oz) bag per week. (She is 11 pounds, and also has 2 wet food meals a day.) It's not cheap, but is a healthy grain-free "dry food" option that my cat really enjoys!
customer_reviews.author: Lauren

customer_reviews.title: My kitty appreciates the food
customer_reviews.text: My cat is pretty fussy about what he eats and this one has his approval. He gets excited even to see a bag--he knows what that is. At first I was not sure if he will take to this food, but after a week of trying to feed him by mixing with other food, he decided he really like the food. He eats them wet as well as dry. The price is a bit high, but I cannot risk my pet health. Thank you for a good product.
customer_reviews.author: Mari

customer_reviews.title: Nutrient dense, happy to have grass-fed for my 12-year-old cat.

The company never got back to me on how they feed their chickens (if they are pastured and not finished with corn or soy). My dog likes it too (sneaky guy...he's allergic to chicken). Wish they had single protein sourced product (lamb-only, beef-only, etc.). Thanks Amazon for carrying this product.
customer_reviews.author: Le Jambon

customer_reviews.title: Quality food, my fussy cat will eat it

I like the ingredients, I think it's a quality cat food altho pricey! but the quality foods are all pricey. So I will continue to buy this food; glad Amazon offers it Subscribe and Save which saves some money.
customer_reviews.author: gracie7

customer_reviews.title: Great food for cats with food allergies!!
customer_reviews.text: My cat loves this food. I use it as a topper on her wet food and also as a treat. It is expensive; however, her overall health has improved.
customer_reviews.author: Janie57

customer_reviews.title: My cats love and and I love the ingrdients!
customer_reviews.text: I feel good giving this to my cats as part of their diet. It is a bit pricy as a food, but their health and lives are worth it to me, as I lost 4 cats in a row to intestinal cancer prior to changing food. Being a dog trainer with education on animal nutrition, this food is the best you can get without making your own!
customer_reviews.author: C. M. Halsey

customer_reviews.title: Healthy alternative to dry kibble for corn allergies
customer_reviews.text: My cat is much healthier on the freeze dried raw food products. She had developed an allergy to corn, which lead to her having painful, loose bowel movements. This product has solved her digestive issues. We are currently feeding the chicken and lamb feast flavor along with 1-1/2 cans of filet and gravy cat food. We have the freeze dried in a dry dish for grazing during the day and feed canned 2-3 times daily. We supplement dry with Blue brand kitty crunchy treats. The cost of an imported freeze dried food is worth it to me.
customer_reviews.author: Kenneth Neely

customer_reviews.title: The cats meow

I am sorry to stop using it, as the quality seems high.

product_meta.title: Feline Natural Grain-Free Freeze Dried Cat Food
feature_bullets: High in meat. Low in carbs. Grain-free. Even the pickiest of eaters are drawn to the natural flavors of Feline Natural. That is because cat’s are genetically predisposed to a diet rich in meat.

Packed full of New Zealand wholefood ingredients, our Feline Natural diets are made from grass-fed free-range meats, cage-free chicken or sustainably caught fish and provide the rich and nourishing proteins and fats needed to give your cat a natural source of energy to thrive.
Inspired by nature, guided by science. For your ultimate peace of mind Feline Natural food meets all AAFCO requirements.
Our minimally processed recipes are made without fillers, legumes, GMO ingredients, starch or preservatives.

Freeze-dried food is the perfect solution to easy storage and transport, giving pet owners the option of providing their pets with a high-meat diet. Use as a complete meal, or sprinkle on top of your cat’s food to use as a tasty topper.
